### Snowflake Endpoints

Your IdP needs these Snowflake URLs:

| Endpoint | URL |
|----------|-----|
| **ACS URL** | `https://{{ snowflake_org_name | lower }}-{{ new_account_name | lower }}.snowflakecomputing.com/fed/login` |
| **Entity ID** | `https://{{ snowflake_org_name | lower }}-{{ new_account_name | lower }}.snowflakecomputing.com` |
| **Login URL** | `https://{{ snowflake_org_name | lower }}-{{ new_account_name | lower }}.snowflakecomputing.com` |

### IdP Configuration Steps

1. In your IdP, create or configure the Snowflake application for this account
2. Set the ACS URL to: `https://{{ snowflake_org_name | lower }}-{{ new_account_name | lower }}.snowflakecomputing.com/fed/login`
3. Set the Entity ID/Audience to: `https://{{ snowflake_org_name | lower }}-{{ new_account_name | lower }}.snowflakecomputing.com`
4. Ensure the NameID format is set to `emailAddress`
5. Assign users in your IdP to access this Snowflake application